// @check
// @error Codegen error
// KNOWN-REMAINING — xfail (ROADMAP A11: "recursion through an **array** element
// (`{ rest: [List] }`)" is listed as REMAINING). This program is SOUND and SHOULD
// compile, but currently CRASHES in codegen. NOT a silent compiler fix — captured
// as an xfail (a codegen-completeness gap on a recursive array-element type).
//
// THE GAP: `Tree` is recursive THROUGH an array element — `kids` is an array of
// `Tree`. Recursion through a *nullable struct field* works (the rec-group ties
// the self-reference, see recursive-type-build-traverse.vl), but recursion
// through the element type of a WasmGC array is not cycle-guarded the same way:
// building the element wasm type re-enters the same `Tree` unboundedly and
// overflows the stack at codegen.
//
// EXPECTED: compiles + runs. ACTUAL: `Codegen error: Maximum call stack size
// exceeded`.
//
// TODO(A11): cycle-guard the array-element type the way the struct rec-group is
// guarded (emit the recursive array type as part of the same rec-group). When
// fixed, flip this to `// @run` and assert a traversal.
type Tree = { value: i32, kids: { [i32]: Tree } | null }
const t: Tree = { value: 1, kids: null }
print(t.value)
